Merry Christmas from the Fulton’s ♥️.
The kids have had a stomach bug basically our whole trip to California. Last night was rough so a black tea latte was a must. This was my first time trying one and it’s so delicious.
The cutest brothers I’ve ever seen 🤍.
The beach just does something for my soul 😌.

Happy Friday 🌼. Oakley was so excited about her flowers. Also I can’t believe my baby is so big. She keeps telling me she wants me to have four babies so each of the kiddos have a baby to play with 🫣😂.

My obsessions lately. 
• If you haven’t tried the @traderjoes boba you definitely should. They are SO good. 
• I’ve been reading so many good books lately but Things We Never Got Over is probably my absolute favorite book I’ve ever read. Every Summer After is a close second. 
• Cadbury Mini Eggs are one of my favorite candies. I just finished Reminders of Him and I loved it. As a mom it really made me feel for her. It’s the first book that actually made me cry lol. 
• I tried a pistachio croissant for the first time when we were in California and I’m so sad I never tried them before. They are so freaking good. 
• The @thealiveapp 💙 it makes working out so fun. Thank you @whitneyysimmons for making a workout app that’s makes me look forward to my workouts.
I can’t get over this pic of me and the boys. They look so tiny 🥺.
Happy Valentine’s Day ❤️. I hope you have an amazing day full of love.

• I’ve been so unmotivated lately to post on here 🫣. Honestly lately, I’d rather sit and read a good book than figure out what to post. 
• Jason had to work on Valentine’s Day so we the weekend before he took the girls on a date and I took the boys. Penelope had to take her baby of course. She gets so mad if you call her baby a doll 😂.
Road trip time 🚙. Jason works over 4 hours from home so we like to visit him at work every once in awhile lol.
Low quality pic but high quality pizza night at daddy’s work. The kiddos had so much fun last night. Have you ever visited a fire station?
Weekend photo dump 📷.
Snow day ⛄️. Actually the kids lasted about 5 minutes. They asked every 5 mins for two hours when they could build a snowman then didn’t even last long enough to make one 🤣.

I decided I’m going to post what I’m currently reading or what’s next on my tbr list on Thursdays lol. I’m a week late but I can’t wait to start reading this today. Things We Never Got Over is my number one favorite book so I’m sure this will be just as amazing. And the fact that a third book is coming out later this year is so exciting 😁. My baby is a second grader 🤍. I can’t believe she’s already done with first grade. This year went by way too fast.

R•O•A•D•T•R•I•P
• I love the idea of a road trip but with four kids it’s not as relaxing as I hoped. No road trip is complete without coffee though. What’s one thing you need during a road trip?
Happy 4th of July friends ♥️🤍💙
My baby is four! Happy 4th birthday Oakley!! I can’t believe you’re already four. We love you so much and hope you have the best birthday.

First day of 2nd grade! I can’t believe I have a 2nd grader. Her teacher is a friend of ours (her hubby works at the station with Jason) so she was very excited. Penelope loves school and I can’t wait to hear all about her first day. Also she wants to be a teacher for babies. Like teach babies who are crawling the alphabet 🤔.

Surprise, we moved!! For the past six years Jason’s been driving almost 5 hours to and from work each week so we decided it was time to move. We’ve been living in a rental for the past two months and escrow finally closed last week 🤍. Now it’s time to diy the heck out of this house and make it exactly what we want.
Always fun visiting daddy at work.
Lake day fun last week. Days like this make me so sad Penelope’s back in school. Always missing my bestie.

I thought I would be getting ready to announce our fifth and final baby but instead I became 1 in 4 women who suffer a miscarriage. We were all so excited. This is probably the hardest thing I’ve ever been through. I know so many of you understand what I’m going through. I know everyone handles this differently but right now it just feels really hard. If anyone else is currently going through this I’m here if you need someone to talk to 🤍. I’m so thankful for friends and family that have been so supportive. @sarah_montoya I couldn’t have gone through this without you.

Merry Christmas Eve 🎄
Cheers to a new year 🥂

2023 was an exciting year but also a heartbreaking year with losing our pup Muffie in July and our miscarriage in August. We moved near Lake Powell in May and finally moved into our new home at the end of July. Penelope started her new school in August and although it’s not as challenging as her old school she’s having so much fun. We had the absolute best time at Disneyland in September and are already dreaming of going back. I can’t wait to see what 2024 brings us. Praying this next year is better than the last.
